deck_excerpt: Actually playing Crossout Designator as a combo piece
deck_description:
I don't know too much about what Kozmo can do, but I definitely know that it is very difficult to actually combine Kozmo and Prediction Princess together into a Deck, even if it is literally just 6 Kozmo cards. I understand that Kozmo has a gameplan where you are focusing on using your pilots to bring out your ships to gain advantage and reduce your opponent's available resources through your various interactions and interruptions. But that doesn't mix well with Prediction Princess, especially after their support. Prediction Princess focuses on getting to Prediction Princess Tarotrei and Prediction Princess Tarotreith in order to set up and build a board of Prediction Princess Ritual Monsters and Flip Monsters over the course of your turn and the start of your opponent's turn with your Flip Monsters either interrupting/stopping your opponent's plays while also netting you card advantage through searches with Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. With the completely opposite-facing ways to faciliate the set-up for both halves of the Deck it's a miracle that I even came up with a way to play Kozmo Prediction Princess. The Level 9 monster we are looking at today is Kozmo Dark Eclipser which is a Level 9 DARK Machine monster. Don't get your hopes up because we are literally incapable of ending on any Kozmo-related plays in our endboard because we just cannot fit the necessary cards to accomplish that in our Deck. We are just using Dark Eclipser and the Kozmo cards we are playing to put a Level 9 on board for World Legacy Monstrosity. I mean, the Deck is fine. It's not great, but it is really funny because we are actually using Crossout Designator as a combo piece in situations where we have access to it. You see, Kozmo Strawman can pay 500 Life Points to target a banished Kozmo monster and Special Summon it with its effect negated, destroying it during the End Phase. So, if we draw a way to get to Strawman, Crossout Designator, and World Legacy Monstrosity, we can Crossout calling Dark Eclipser and banish a copy of it from the Deck, Normal Summon Strawman and pay 500 to bring back the banished Dark Eclipser, and activate Monstrosity targeting Dark Eclipser to get Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck, giving you Rank 9 access for Mereologic Aggregator and Bibliomuse to faciliate your Prediction Princess plays. Again, the Deck is alright. It at least functions and you have a decent chance of opening full combo, whether it is purely just Prediction Princess plays or the Kozmo line to Dark Eclipser and then to your Prediction Princess. 

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on the field face-up or face-down, and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. Tarotreith must be either Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect allows you to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from your GY if she was tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she is face-up on the field, she gives your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 Trias Hierarchia to be sent off of the Diviners we are playing and it can Special Summon itself from hand or GY by tributing a Fairy monster. This basically can give you Rank 9 access, given you draw Diviner and Monstrosity as you can get Deus-X and Dark Eclipser off of Monstrosity targeting it on field. Speaking of, 2 Kozmo Dark Eclipser. This card cannot be targeted by your opponent's card effects and non-opt, during either player's turn, when a Trap Card is activated, you can banish a Kozmo from GY to negate the activation and destroy that card. And if it is destroyed by battle or card effect and sent to GY, you can banish it to add a Level 8 or lower Kozmo monster from Deck. This card is neat in Kozmo Decks, but we are just playing it as a Level 9. We are playing 2 because Crossout Designator only banishes from Deck and since it doesn't hurt if we draw 1 of them because Strawman, like all the Kozmo pilots, can banish themselves to Special Summon a ship from hand. 1 Kozmo Farmgirl which can banish itself during either player's turn to Special Summon a Level 4 or higher Kozmo monster from hand and if it inflicts battle damage to your opponent, you can pay 500 to search for a Kozmo card. I mean we are just playing Farmgirl as another pilot. I just felt like the Deck needed another pilot to potentially draw into, so Farmgirl is keeping Strawman company. And we are never using that second effect because it's gonna be pretty hard to inflict battle damage with 1500 ATK, and it's not like you can enter battle during turn 1 either way. 3 Kozmo Strawman who has the same first effect as Farmgirl, just Special Summoning Level 3 or higher Kozmo monsters from hand instead. And you can pay 500 Life Points once per turn to target and Special Summon a banished Kozmo monster with its effects negated, destroying it during the End Phase. 3 Diviner of the Herald which sends a Fairy monster from Deck or Extra Deck to GY on Normal or Special Summon to increase its Level by the Level of the sent monster which you are using to send either Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck or Trias Hierarchia from Deck. And finally, 2 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring as potential handtraps, but mainly to add more use to our Crossouts. 

Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Emergency Teleport which gets us any of our Kozmo pilots from Deck. 3 Crossout Designator which allows you to declare a card name and banish that declared card from your Main Deck to negate its effects and the activated effect and effects on field of cards with the same original name. Usually, you are using this against handtraps, but we are using it to banish Dark Eclipser, and not being able to activate its effects doesn't matter at all as we are never using them either way. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess from Deck face-down. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which can either Special Summon a Level 9 from hand or target a Level 9 you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster, but with different names. And finally, 3 Infinite Impermanence. We are not playing Gold Sarcophagus because it's only at 1, meaning that we have a large chance of not drawing it, and while it does also banish a monster from Deck, leaving a potential Crossout in hand to deal with a potential handtrap, I just find it not very good as Crossout. Crossout can banish a card from Deck and can protect you, both being in different applications and situations of course, but drawing Gold Sarc when you have full Prediction Princess combo without the use of your Kozmo cards, leaves it sitting there all stupid. Crossout just feels better to play and has more usage overall, especially when you don't have access to the Kozmo part of your Deck. Sure, it might give you another way to banish a monster from Deck, but it's not "that" good to consider also playing it. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 1 Super Starslayer TY-PHON - Sky Crisis. 1 Infinitrack Earth Slicer. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Nine-Lives Cat. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows, and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Underworld Goddess of the Closed World, 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 2 Droll & Lock Bird, 2 Triple Tactics Talent, 2 Lightning Storm, 3 Dark Ruler No More, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_excerpt: Combining both Jake Stox's list and any hand loop list, here is Modern VW Handloop V1.0
deck_description:
Inspired by a Virtual World list by Norwich Regional 5th placer Jake Stox and other VW hand loop lists, the goal with this list is simple: try to make a very consistent hand loop "FTK."

There are a couple of cards that I'm considering putting in: Overdrive Teleporter, more copies of Wheeleler and Tracker, and Trishula (especially since Tear is a deck that exists and in the case that I'm going second I'm going to need to get rid of some cards on board).

There are a few glaring problems with the deck that I intend to fix:

  1. Quem is in the format.
  2. This is a going-first deck.
  3. Beast of the Pharaoh is a Zombie, not a psychic.

deck_name: Beginner's Guide to Infernoble (feat. Pak's YCS List)
deck_excerpt: Combining DUNE with AGOVE support, Infernoble has consistently become a top finisher in YCS!
deck_description:
Combining Duelist Nexus with Age of Overlord support, Infernoble has consistently become a top finisher in YCS! A new win condition under the form of Emperor Charles the Great, consistency boosters comparable to Isolde being Angelica - Princess of Noble Arms, busted S/T negation with Angelic Ring (negates stuff like Dark Ruler and Super Poly), and extra starters with the Sinful Spoils package! This increase of power and consistency comes with the ability to stuff the deck with a ton of staples while still being playable - enabling a fearsome combo deck with power to rival the historical figure Charles the Great!

 

It seems that Infernoble has gained a new powerful identify when compared to it's hand-looping, generic boss monster turboing predecessor back with its release with Rise of the Duelist at 2020. The recent support for this deck has once again reached critical mass for competitive play, enabling Infernoble to play as a top meta contender. The boards this deck generates are unique, interesting and ridiculously powerful! 

 

The decklist in this guide inspired by Pak's top YCS Richmond and YCS Bologna finish with Infernoble. He explains everything in-depth, his theorycrafting and combos with his Youtube video much better than I can with this written article. Be sure to check it out!

 

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 
ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING
 
The structure of the standard INFERNOBLE deck changes dramatically after Age of Overlord. The Infernoble core is very compact since every combo piece is highly searchable (via Isolde, Museum and Sinful Spoils), allowing the maindeck knights to be 1-ofs. The Noble Knight starters are 3-ofs with Arms Museum also searchable with Terraforming. 3 Heritage of the Chalice searches for any Noble Knight monster or Noble Arms. Finally, 1 ROTA gets any warrior monster. 
 
Age of Overlord also brings the SINFUL SPOILS engine to Infernoble, allowing for another layer of consistency. The Sinful Spoils package is primarily used for WANTED: Seeker to search for Diabellstar, so she can set Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye from deck. Snake-Eye summons from deck a level 1 Fire monster, that being either Infernoble Knight Renaud or Fire Flint Lady. All of this does not use up your valuable normal summon allowing for an easier way to get to Isolde! Finally, WANTED: Seeker recycles Original Sinful Spoils for a 1 card draw. 
 
There are 6 EQUIP spells in this deck, and they are mostly garnets to be sent to the GY via Isolde. During the End Phase, these equips (usually Angelic Ring) is equipped to Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. You may not want to draw into these garnets, but Infernoble Arms - Durendal is fine to draw into (hence it's a 2-of) since it searches for a level 5 or lower Fire Warrior from deck. 
 
Finally, there are 12 STAPLE slots in this deck. These staples can be exchanged with the Side Deck! 
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
Infernoble's gameplan is to create a unbreakable board that your opponent simply cannot hope to play through. It generally ends on 2-3 spell/trap negates, 1 quick effect pop, and 1 monster negate/destroy. If there are extenders, the board can also have Baronne, S:P Little Knight and Apollousa. 

There are multiple pathways to respectable Infernoble boards that all vary in power depending on how many times you've been interrupted and whatever cards you have in your hand. However, they all centre around resolving both of Isolde's effects. If Isolde is interrupted, the backup plan is to summon S:P Little Knight. 
 
The 12 handtraps maindecked should hopefully be enough to simplify the gamestate so that S:P can control your opponent until you can full combo with Isolde. 
 
Here is the Infernoble 1-card combo:
 
Neo-Space Connector = Emperor Charles the Great (Pop 1 card, spell/trap negate destroy) + Angelica's Angel Ring (Spell speed 4 mandatory spell negate) + Phoenix Gearfried (monster negate destroy) + S:P Little Knight (target monster banish) + Angelica (If targeted, GY set-up and banishes herself until end phase) + potential hand rip and hand knowledge (Aqua Dolphin's optional effect) + draw 1
  1. Normal summon Connector.  Activate Connector's on-summon effect to summon Aqua Dolphin from deck. 
  2. Activate Aqua Dolphin's effect to look at your opponent's hand and hand-rip a card from it (if applicable, and sniping their droll/ash is optimal). 
  3. Link summon Isolde using Connector + Aqua Dolphin. 
  4. Activate Isolde's on-summon effect to search for Fire Flint Lady. 
  5. Activate Isolde's effect sending Phoenix Blade, Angelica's Angelic Ring, D.D.R. - Different Dimension Reincarnation and Infernoble Arms - Durendal to summon Infernoble Knight Ogier from deck. 
  6. Activate Ogier's on-summon effect to send Infernoble Knight Turpin from deck to GY. 
  7. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Connector and Aqua Dolphin. 
  8. Equip Ogier with Phoenix Blade. 
  9. Activate Turpin's effect from the GY to summon itself since you control a monster equipped with a card. 
  10. XYZ summon Battlin' Boxer King Dempsey using Ogier + Turpin. Activate Dempsey's on-summon effect to search for Infernoble Knight Renaud from deck. 
  11. Special summon Renaud. Activate Renaud's on-summon effect to recover Different Dimension Reincarnation from GY to hand. 
  12. Activate Different Dimension Reincarnation discarding Fire Flint Lady to summon from banished pile Connector. 
  13. Synchro summon Anglica, Princess of Noble Arms using Renaud + Connector. Activate Angelica's on-summon effect to search for Noble Arms Museum. 
  14. Activate Noble Arms Museum. Activate Museum's effect paying 1200 LP to search for Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  15. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Connector and Fire Flint Lady. 
  16. CL2 equip Anglica with Phoenix Blade and CL2 activate Angelica's effect to send Pheonix Gearfried to the to GY, banish herself and summon from Extra Deck Infernoble Knight Roland.
  17. Activate Dempsey's effect by detaching Turpin. 
  18. Activate Turpin's effect, equiping him to Infernoble Knight Roland. 
  19. Activate Noble Arms Museum's effect to special summon Turpin from the backrow. 
  20. Synchro Summon Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles using Turpin + Roland. 
  21. Equip Almace to Emperor Charles. 
  22. Link summon Emperor Charles the Great using Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  23. CL1 Emperor Charles the Great's effect to target equip Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles in the GY, CL2 Almace's effect to target and add back to hand Phoenix Gearfried from GY.
  24. Link summon S:P Little Knight using Isolde + Dempsey. 
  25. Special summon Phoenix Gearfried by banishing Infernoble Arms - Durendal from GY.
  26. Activate Ogier's effect in the GY to equip itself to Emperor Charles the Great. 
  27. During the endphase, Angelica summons herself back to the field. 
  28. During the endphase, Emperor Charles the Great activates his effect (these effects were obtained from the equipped Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles) to equip Angelica's Angelic Ring from the GY and Infernoble Knight Maugis. 
  29. Emperor Charles the Great's trigger effect activates, destroying Maugis. 
  30. Maugis' trigger effect activates, shuffling back to deck from banished pile Infernoble Arms - Durendal, Infernoble Arms - Almace and Fire Flint Lady to draw 1 card. 
  31. During your opponent's main phase, you can equip Infernoble Knight Roland to Emperor Charles the Great to trigger his destruction effect. 
From merely 1 card, the Infernoble player has summoned an army of monsters with more interactions than the opponent has cards in their hand (especially if you hand-ripped earlier)! This uninterrupted 1 card combo is currently unparallelled in this age of modern Yugioh - it's so ridiculously strong, which is befitting a deck based on Charles the Great. But hold on, this gets better with the Sinful Spoils engine!   
 
Diabellestarr + Any fire warrior + 1 discard = Emperor Charles the Great (Pop 1 card, spell/trap negate destroy) + Angelica's Angel Ring (Spell speed 4 mandatory spell negate) + Phoenix Gearfried (monster negate destroy) + 3 material Apollousa (3 monster negates) + Angelica (If targeted, GY set-up and banishes herself until end phase) + potential hand rip and hand knowledge (Aqua Dolphin's optional effect) + draw 1
  1. Normal summon fire warrior. 
  2. Special summon Diabellestar by discarding 1 card. Activate Diabellestar's on-summon effect setting from deck Original Sinful Spoils - Snake-Eye. 
  3. Activate Original Sinful Spoils by sending Diabellestar to the GY to summon from deck Infernoble Knight Ricciardetto. 
  4. Link summon Isolde using fire warrior + Ricciardetto. 
  5. Activate Isolde's on-summon effect to search for Connector. 
  6. Activate Isolde's effect sending Phoenix Blade, Angelica's Angelic Ring, D.D.R. - Different Dimension Reincarnation and Infernoble Arms - Durendal to summon Infernoble Knight Ogier from deck. 
  7. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Ricciardetto and fire warrior. 
  8. Equip Ogier with Phoenix Blade. 
  9. Activate Turpin's effect from the GY to summon itself since you control a monster equipped with a card. 
  10. XYZ summon Battlin' Boxer King Dempsey using Ogier + Turpin. Activate Dempsey's on-summon effect to search for Infernoble Knight Renaud from deck. 
  11. Special summon Renaud. Activate Renaud's on-summon effect to recover Different Dimension Reincarnation from GY to hand.
  12. Link summon a 2400ATK Apollousa using Isolde + Renaud + Dempsey.
  13. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Isolde and Dempsey.
  14. Activate Different Dimension Reincarnation discarding Phoenix Blade to summon from banished pile Ricciardetto.
  15. Activate Ricciardetto's on-summon effect to summon from GY Turpin. 
  16. Synchro summon Anglica, Princess of Noble Arms using Ricciardetto + Turpin. Activate Angelica's on-summon effect to search for Noble Arms Museum. 
  17. Activate Noble Arms Museum. Activate Museum's effect paying 1200 LP to search for Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  18. Activate Phoenix Blade's effect in the GY to add to your hand by banishing Ricciardetto and Renaud. 
  19. CL2 equip Anglica with Phoenix Blade and CL2 activate Angelica's effect to send Pheonix Gearfried to the to GY, banish herself and summon from Extra Deck Infernoble Knight Roland.
  20. Equip Roland with Infernoble Arms - Almace. 
  21. Activate Turpin's effect, equiping him to Infernoble Knight Roland. 
  22. Activate Noble Arms Museum's effect to special summon Turpin from the backrow. 
  23. Synchro Summon Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles using Turpin + Roland. 
  24. Activate Almace's effect to target and add back to hand Phoenix Gearfried from GY.
  25. Activate Roland's effect in the GY to equip himself to Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  26. Link summon Emperor Charles the Great using Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles. 
  27. Activate Emperor Charles the Great's on-summon effect to target equip Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles in the GY.
  28. Activate Ogier's effect in the GY to equip itself to Emperor Charles the Great. 
  29. Special summon Phoenix Gearfried by banishing Infernoble Arms - Durendal from GY.
  30. During the endphase, Angelica summons herself back to the field. 
  31. During the endphase, Emperor Charles the Great activates his effect (these effects were obtained from the equipped Infernoble Knight Emperor Charles) to equip Angelica's Angelic Ring from the GY and Infernoble Knight Maugis. 
  32. Emperor Charles the Great's trigger effect activates, destroying Maugis. 
  33. Maugis' trigger effect activates, shuffling back to deck from banished pile Infernoble Arms - Durendal, Infernoble Arms - Almace and fire warrior to draw 1 card. 
  34. During your opponent's main phase, you can equip Infernoble Knight Roland to Emperor Charles the Great to trigger his destruction effect.
GENERAL TIPS
  • Being a combo deck, Infernoble functions like Mannadium, Dragonlink and Cyberse Mathmech. They can all create scary boards, but kind of suck going 2nd. The 12 handtraps coupled with the amount of gas Infernoble has theoretically should enable this deck to simplify the gamestate, play through interruption and full combo, but if you know for sure you can't make it through what your opponent has, just go to next game. It's better that you take the loss and not give your opponent any information so they don't side the right cards against this strategy. 
  • The backup for this strategy if you can't resolve Isolde is S:P Little Knight! You can even link away S:P Little Knight to make Isolde the following turn when it's safer to do so. That's why there are two S:Ps in the Extra Deck (ouch that's expensive for IRL decks lol). 
  • You can make Baronne before Isolde with Diabellestarr + Ash Blossom. Baronne can also be made with Infernoble Knight Charles + a level 1 tuner like Ricardetto or Renaud. 
  • Noble Arms Musuem is a soft once per turn. Multiple Museums means you can summon up to two Emperor Charles the Great! Be sure to not link off Isolde for S:P until you have both Charles on field, since you need Isolde's link zones to summon two of them. 
  • If you have a garnet you wanted to search in your opening hand, try to get the card in the GY somehow (either by using it, discarding it for Neo Aqua Dolphin or Different Dimension Reincarnation's effect). Then you get Infernoble Knight Maugis in the GY to shuffle it back so you can properly search the garnet later in your combo. 
  • In games 2 and 3, side in Called By the Grave with Crossout Designator since your opponent is also siding in handtraps (like the fearsome Droll) to hardcounter your strategy. 
  • Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
CONCLUDING REMARKS
 
As a history nerd, the chance to field Charles the Great is like a dream come true! And he really does live up to his "The Great" title, since this boss monster (coupled with his bestie S:P Little Knight) is enough to boost this strategy to meta relevance once again! The consistency that the Diabellestarr engine and the new Infernoble cards of Museum and Angelica really push the deck to the next level of power since it allows so much staple cards to be used with the deck like the 12 handtraps. Perhaps now Charles the Great can be revered and respected as much as his historical counterpart in our favourite children's card game Yugioh. As this deck's pilot, can you live up to the greatness of his name?
 
GLHF Duelists!

Not really sure how viable this deck is but I thought it would be fun to make a deck out of a seemilgly weak card/archetype. There has been a ton of support for these cards so even though they look cute, best to tread carefully!

deck_excerpt: Making use of Over Future Fusion
deck_description:
The Level 9 monster we are looking at today is Chimeratech Overdragon which is a Level 9 DARK Machine Fusion Monster that requires Cyber Dragon and 1 or more Machine monsters as Fusion Material. Look, I know that we are focusing on trying to Summon Overdragon in this Deck, so a Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess Deck is a possibility. However, it would never come into fruition. There are 2 reasons for this. First of all, all of the good Cyber Dragon cards and Cyber Spell/Traps Machine-lock you. This is a bit of a stretch but cards like Cybernetic Horizon, Cyber Dragon Nachster, and Cyber Dragon Herz all have good effects for either Cyber Dragon plays or are able to really turbo your way to Overdragon, but they Machine-lock you. I'm not saying that they are particularly good (in the case of Cybernetic Horizon in the bricks you need to play) or what you would theoretically play in a Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess Deck, but I would've liked to experiment with it as a Deck at the very least, either having like a Cyber Dragon Infinity (or idk Cybernetic Overflow?) as a part of my endboard or having the ability to go into a Chimeratech Rampage Dragon on my following turn for a Quick OTK. Second, have you read what Overdragon does? It sends your entire board other than itself to the GY on Fusion Summon. Even if you were able to make some assemblance of a Cyber Dragon board before going into your Prediction Princess plays, Overdragon just throws it all into the GY when its Summoned as a mandatory effect. And so I have ended up with this Deck that intends on turboing out Overdragon for a Level 9 on field for World Legacy Monstrosity, and to be fair, it's probably better than what Cyber Dragon Prediction Princess would've been. We are utilizing Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio and Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra to search for the current OCG-exclusive Over Future Fusion. I mean if this card doesn't scream "Make Chimeratech Overdragon", I don't know what does (probably Cybernetic Horizon actually). It reads that you can activate each of its effects once per turn. You can reveal a Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck and send a named Fusion Material monster from your Deck to GY, but you cannot Special Summon monsters with that name nor activate their monster effects this turn. And you can also Fusion Summon a DARK Machine Fusion Monster from your Extra Deck by banishing materials from your GY. This means that we can make Overdragon and go through our whole Prediction Princess line through a 2.5 card combo of Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio, World Legacy Monstrosity, and a monster to discard for Scorpio. Normal Summon Scorpio and discard a monster to Special Summon Cobra from Deck. Cobra searches for Over Future Fusion. Activate Over Future Fusion and use its first effect to dump Cyber Dragon from Deck. Link off Cobra and Scorpio into Sky Striker Ace - Camellia which is a generic Link-2 Machine monster. Then we Link off Camellia for any Sky Striker Link-1, I am playing Sky Striker Ace - Kagari. This gets Camellia into GY, giving you Cydra and a Machine in GY, so now you can activate Over Future Fusion's second effect to banish Cydra and Camellia to Fusion Summon Overdragon. Overdragon sends the rest of your field to the GY, and now you activate Monstrosity targeting Overdragon for Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler and you should know the rest. I mean, the Deck is cool, but I'd much rather be playing a more interesting Prediction Princess variant that actually has the ability to produce more of a unique endboard. 

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on the field face-up or face-down, and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. Tarotreith must be either Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect allows you to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from your GY if she was tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she is face-up on the field, she gives your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 Mardel, Generaider Boss of Light which can be Summoned off of the Lonefire Blossoms we are playing for a Level 9 and on Normal or Special Summon, it can search a Generaider card or a Plant monster. She also works as a nice Small World bridge from Diviner to her to a Predaplant or Lonefire. 2 Cyber Dragon. You realistically only need 1, but Over Future Fusion only does send from Deck. Even if you draw 1 copy, you can still use it as a Small World bridge from it to Mardel to Diviner or a Predaplant or Lonefire. 3 Predaplant Ophrys Scorpio which sends a monster from hand or GY on Normal or Special Summon to Special Summon a Predaplant from Deck. 1 Predaplant Darlingtonia Cobra which adds a Fusion of Polymerization Spell card from your Deck to your hand once per Duel if it is Special Summoned by the effect of a Predaplant monster. 2 Lonefire Blossom which can Tribute a Plant to Special Summon a Plant from Deck. 3 Diviner of the Herald which sends a Fairy from Deck or Extra Deck to GY to increase its Level by the Level of the sent monster. It's good for Small World bridging and you can just Normal Summon it to send Herald of the Arc Light from Extra Deck for a Ritual search to go through your Ritual plays from there. And finally, 3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring. 

For Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Over Future Fusion. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down, and you can also banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which Special Summons a Level 9 from hand or targets a Level 9 you control and Special Summons 2 Level 9's from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster, but with different names. And finally, 3 Small World. 

Extra Deck: 1 Chimeratech Overdragon, 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon, and 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck if sent to GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess and 1 Cross-Sheep to get more use out of Scorpio and Cobra through searching for Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 1 S:P Little Knight and 1 I:P Masquerena. 1 Sky Striker Ace - Camellia and 1 Sky Striker Ace - Kagari. Camellia is just a generic Link-2 Machine that we can easily Link off since all of the Sky Striker Link-1's just need a Sky Striker monster that isn't their Attribute as material. This gets you a Machine into GY for Over Future Fusion to get you Overdragon. I am choosing to play Kagari, and while you can send a Sky Striker Spell from Deck to GY with Camellia and add it back to hand upon Link Summoning Kagari, there is never going to be a moment where we don't have a monster in our Main Monster Zones, meaning that we can't make use of any of the Sky Striker Spells, even if we wanted to. But you could play any Sky Striker Link-1 that you fancy. Finally, 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 2 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Triple Tactics Thrust, 1 Triple Tactics Talent, 2 Infinite Impermanence, and 3 Evenly Matched.

Branded in High spirit synergizes well with the Swordsoul, as putting one and Icejade can let Taia do its thing. Lastly, Ecclesia is an all-around all star in this strategy, fueling both paths and easily coming back in one's hand

deck_excerpt: Firery flames engulf wraithsoth as a new deck is born!
deck_description: a quaint deck i made usng my spoils (heh) of using the pack simulator (do not build it is very expensive)

ok so this idea wasn't mine but i built the deck from scratch, trying to optimize it as much as possible. The vanilla vaalmonica combo is
Dimonno Vaalmonica or Angello Vaalmonica -> Vaalmonica Scelta -> Vaalmonica, the Agathokakological Voice -> another Dimonno -> pendulum summon Dimonno -> copy Scelta to grab Vaalmonica Versare -> ditch a trap card, you could choose between Vaalmonica Followed Rhythm or Vaalmonica Chosen Melody (i use followed). The only problem of this combo is that it totally ignores the aromages and makes you start with -2000 lp

the aromage combo is One for One  / Lonefire Blossom  / other shenanigans to summon Aromalylith Rosalina -> Aromage Laurel -> Aromaseraphy Jasmine -> Therion "Lily" Borea -> Therion Discolosseum -> Cattycorn if you have no cards on the field, to grab the vaalmonica field spell and autopilot vaalmonicas before continuing the combo, or Aromaseraphy Angelica to extend it with a synchro summon -> Aromalylith Rosemary to grab Aroma Blend , discard Discolosseum and set Humid Winds , then fusion summon Aromalylith Magnolia / activate angelica and other "if you have more lp" effects, activate ONLY the first effect of Humid winds to grab Aromage Marjoram , activate the second effect to special summon it using rosemary, synchro summon Aromaseraphy Sweet Marjoram with marjoram and angelica or other shenanigans, grab Blessed Winds and set it. If you did everything correctly, you should end up with a standard aromage board, + two pendulum vaalmonicas with x2/3 counters on angel

in the side deck cactus bouncer is used as a start first special summon negate, even if you'll develop a weaker board. Child's play can be replaced with evenly matched, but it works well with the rest of the deck and it's fun if the opponent can't read

deck_excerpt: Relay Soul Win ft. Graceful Tear
deck_description:
Hello there! It has been a while since I showcased a Treasure Panda deck. Here, you will win with Relay Soul. Yes, I said win, you heard me right. So, why don't you keep reading?

 

 

Gameplan

1) When Baronne is present, Special Summon Banisher with Saryuja. Then, Special Summon Chaos Emperor Dragon with its ability. Your Primal Seed loop is ready.

2) Play D.D. Designator until you deplete your opponent's resources in-hand. Then, play Temple >>> Graceful combo to give your opponent Relay Soul.

3) Play Offerings on Baronne. Then, activate D.D.R on Baronne. This step is needed to not deck-out. You can also destroy Temple with Baronne.

4) Set Primal Seed + Drop Off + Graceful Tear and end your turn. On your opponent's Draw Phase, activate Drop Off. If needed, negate whatever your opponent can activate with Baronne in response to Drop Off, just in case.

5) If your opponent sets Relay Soul, which was given in #2, you can give a monster to them with Graceful Tear when it's your turn.

6) From here on, there are three possible options...

  • Your opponent concedes, which can happen most of the time even before all of that.
  • Your opponent doesn't use anything given to them. In that case, attack directly for the win.
  • Your opponent activates Relay Soul. If it occurs, you can destroy that monster with Baronne. A rare sight to behold but a great one nonetheless.

7) Congratulations, you have won with Relay Soul!

- "Temple of the Kings" can be found within "Guardian of Kings" Secret Pack to save 30 SR! As of this writing, you can also find this card in "The Ones Who Serve Ra" Timed Pack.

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Graceful Tear" + "Relay Soul" + "Drop Off" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 150 SR and 60 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 660 SR and 150 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_name: Zoodiac comback!! and Combo KASHTIRA ZOODIAC was born - DUELIST CUP 2023
deck_description: On December 5, Master Duel officially applied a new banlist and in this banlist update two Zoodiac cards were unbanned. Those are Ratpier and Zoodiac Barrage. So the zoodiac deck will change like that with the return of these two cards. Today I will review using the KASHTIRA ZOODIAC deck. Below is the deckprofile for everyone's reference.
prog 6a

I thought I already put this out, but I apparently didn't: Here is Gagaga Prediction Princess. This Deck focuses on Gagaga Caesar as its effect allows you to once per turn banish a monster from your GY with a Level to change the Levels of all Gagaga monsters you control to that monster's Level. With Onomat's innate ability to search out a lot of Gagaga, Dododo, Zubaba, and Gogogo monsters, when we pair that up with Gagaga's ability to just Special Summon their monsters from hand with the greatest of ease, we have a lot of material actually on the board to get our plays started. But that still leaves one question that needs to be answered: "How are we getting a Level 9 into the GY for Caesar to banish?" Well, that's simple, we play Foolish Burial and Dragon Shrine to dump our 1 copy of World Legacy Guardragon Mardark from Deck to GY. "But what happens if you draw it?" Well, just become better and don't draw it. It's just that easy. This Deck is so incredibly gimmicky, but it would be a shame if I didn't at least mention it because it is just so fun and goofy to play. And because we are fully capable of getting 3 or 4 Gagagas onto the field, we end up with material to either first make a copy of Sacred Tree Beast, Hyperyton to prevent ourselves from being handtrapped or Nibirued or we can end on a Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows to go into a Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity if need be. Is this Deck any good? I mean, it depends on your definition of good, but this Deck really does work. I still like the euphoria of activating a copy of World Legacy Monstrosity, but just being able to faciliate a Prediction Princess combo through cards you'd never thought'd be included in a Prediction Princess Deck is just as good. 

For the monsters, you already know them: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse, and 2 Deus-X Krawler. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on field face-up or face-down and she can also Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down during your End Phase. Tarotreith must either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect Special Summons a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from the GY face-down if she was Tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect allows you to search for a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from your Deck to your hand, and while she is face-up on the field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. Deus-X negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. 1 World Legacy Guardragon Mardark. Just don't draw it. For our Gagaga/Onomats: 1 Utopic Onomatopoeia, 3 Zubababancho Gagagacoat, 3 Gagaga Caesar, 3 Gagaga Child, and 3 Gagaga Clerk. Utopic Onomatopoeia can Special Summon up to 1 each of a Gagaga, Zubaba, Gogogo, and/or Dododo monster from your hand except itself in Defense, Xyz locking you for the rest of the turn. Xyz-locking you prevents you from Linking off your Mereologic Aggregator with a Herald of the Arc Light attached into Gravity Controller. But that isn't too much of a problem as if you get 3 additional Gagagas onto field and Caesar turns them all into Level 9's, you can go into a Phantom Fortress Enterblathnir in addition to Aggregator to rip a card out of your opponent's hand, send Herald for a search, reattach it, and Xyz both into Number F0: Utopic Future and then into Number F0: Utopic Draco Future. However, while Utopic Draco Future has the benefit of being a monster negate and an indestructible body on field, do we really need a monster negate when we have Deus-X Krawler access? It's totally something that you can do in this Deck and we are playing the cards to do that, but I just feel like Utopic Onomat can only be used as a Gagaga in name to put on field because there are going to be very few instances where we can actually get 3 other Gagagas on field to go through this line. I think that 1 is enough for that and as an additional search target for Onomatoparia. Zubababancho Gagagacoat can Special Summon itself from han dif you control a Zubaba or Gagaga monster and you can also target a Dododo or Gogogo monster in GY and Special Summon it, Xyz locking you for the rest of the turn. This card is just a Gagaga that can Summon itself for free from hand which is good for getting Gagaga names onto field for Caesar. And while it's second effect isn't too relevant since we aren't actually playing Onomat, it can still bring back a Utopic Onomatopoeia if that's in GY. Caesar can banish a monster with a Level from GY to make all Gagagas you currently control become that monster's Level. Just note that you may not find a way to get a Level 9 into the GY. Your options are Foolish Burial or Dragon Shrine to dump World Legacy Guardragon Mardark, but you can also discard 1 with Onomatoparia. Just be aware that it may not always be possible. Child can Special Summon itself for free from hand if you control another Gagaga monster and if it is Summoned this way you can target a Gagaga you control with a different Level for this card to become the Level of that card. We are just using this card as a free Gagaga name we can Summon. Clerk can non-once per turn Special Summon herself from hand if you control a different Gagaga monster. Another free Summon to put more names on field. 

For Spell/Traps: 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Dragon Shrine and 1 Foolish Burial. 1 Reinforcement of the Army. 3 Onomatoparia which can discard a card to add 2 monsters that are a Zubaba, Gagaga, Gogogo, or Dododo monster, but you add 1 from each category. 2 Onomatopickup which we are only using for its effect on activation which allows you to add an Onomat card from Deck to hand. This gets you either Onomatopickup or Utopic Onomatopoeia. Finally, 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can also banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. 

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 1 Infinitrack Earth Slicer. 1 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Phantom Fortress Enterblathnir which detaches a material to banish a card your opponent controls, a random card from their hand, a card from their GY, or the top card of their Deck face-up. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 Sacred Tree Beast, Hyperyton, 1 Number F0: Utopic Draco Future, and 1 Number F0: Utopic Future. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 1 Kurikara Divincarnate, 2 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Lightning Storm, 1 Harpie's Feather Duster, 3 Evenly Matched, and 3 Solemn Judgment.

deck_excerpt: The things I do for a Level 9...
deck_description:
I never knew a single lick of F.A. before trying to build F.A. Prediction Princess. The only card I knew was F.A. Dawn Dragster, but looking up all of the Level 9 monsters in the game introduced me to F.A. Motorhome Transport. Motorhome Transport is a Level 9 LIGHT Machine Synchro Monster. But here is the catch: We aren't Summoning him as our Level 9 in this Deck. You could Summon him as your Level 9, but realistically, why would you? The thing about F.A. is that you really need to be popping your Field Spells (other than Hyper Stadium) in order to be searching for the F.A. cards you actually need, but at the same time, you only have 2 good Level 4 F.A. monsters and at least need 1 of them along with access to F.A. Auto Navigator in order to really go through with Synchro plays in the Deck. What I am trying to say is that F.A. realistically is only able to pop off if you open a lot of their cards along with ways to actually go into Synchros. There are several things that we need to take into consideration. First, if you want to consistently make Synchros, you need Auto Navigator in order to reset your F.A. monster's Levels so that you can access the Synchros you actually want. Second, you want to at least open 2 Field Spells with one of them being U.A. Hyper Stadium with the other being some other F.A. Field Spell. This is less consistent than before due to Terraforming now being limited as opposed to being unlimited when the Deck released. Also, Destrudo, the Lost Dragon's Frisson and Ancient Fairy Dragon, while they are good for this Deck, it does take a lot of space in the Deck to consistently always access Destrudo and it really takes away from our goal of playing F.A. Prediction Princess because Ancient Fairy and Destrudo lean more towards you investing in playing F.A. and not helping you get to a Level 9 for Prediction Princess. And third, it is really hard to ensure that your F.A. monsters' Levels stay at the amount that you want them to stay at. All of the F.A. Field Spells other than Hyper Stadium increase your F.A. monsters' Levels by 2. Imagine finally being able to Synchro Summon into Motorhome and it ending up as a Level 11 on field due to your Field Spell. Now you need a way to get rid of your Field Spell or use Auto Nav's effect to return Motorhome's Level back to 9. But then you realize that you can just make Dawn Dragster which is a Level 7 which becomes a Level 9 under a Field Spell. Well yes, but now we come to the point where we, again, need Auto Nav, to return an F.A.'s Level to normal in order to access Dawn Dragster. And with Auto Nav being the only Tuner in Deck and with no real "good" way to pop our F.A. Field Spells to search, actually having it is pretty rare. So this Deck is what I have come up with. It makes the best that it can out of the F.A. monsters to get 2 Level 9's out onto the field without World Legacy Monstrosity, but we are still playing it to have more opportunities to go even harder in. With this Deck, you really have to play with your hand and finagle your plays to hopefully get to where you need to go. Our usual combo is a 3-card combo consisting of: any Level 4 F.A. monster, U.A. Hyper Stadium, and an F.A. Field Spell that is not Hyper Stadium. Let's say you have F.A. Whip Crosser, Hyper Stadium, and F.A. City Grand Prix. Normal Summon Whip Crosser and activate Hyper Stadium. Hyper Stadium searches F.A. Dark Dragster from Deck and you choose to increase Whip Crosser's Level by 1, making it a Level 5. Activate Hyper Stadium's other effect to reveal City Grand Prix in hand and pay 1000 to have an Extra Normal Summon of an F.A. or U.A. during your Main Phase this turn. Increase Whip Crosser's Level by 1, making it Level 6. Activate City Grand Prix, increasing Whip Crosser by 2 Levels, making it a Level 8. Then also, increase its Level by 1 again by its own effect to make it a Level 9. Since you have a Level 7 or higher F.A. on field, Special Summon Dark Dragster from hand. Now, if you don't have World Legacy Monstrosity, just overlay Dark Dragster and Whip Crosser into Aggregator and go from there. If you have Monstrosity, Summon Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck. Overlay Deus-X and Whip Crosser into Aggregator. Then, decrease Dark Dragster's Level by 3 to pop City Grand Prix. City Grand Prix adds F.A. Auto Navigator from Deck to hand on destruction. Based on what you have in hand as your last card, there are a few things you could do, but from here, increase Dark Dragster's Level by 1, making it a Level 5. Extra Normal Summon Auto Nav and use its effect to add F.A. Off-Road Grand Prix. Activate Off-Road Grand Prix which increases the Level of all your F.A.'s by 2, making Auto Nav into a Level 3 and Dark Dragster into a Level 7. Now you can Synchro for Baronne de Fleur. It's very difficult to play this Deck to where you want it to end up, but you just need to play with whatever you draw to the best of your ability. 

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei can Quick Effect flip a monster on the field face-up or face-down, and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down. Tarotreith must be either Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei's End Phase effect. Her Flip Effect allows you to Special Summon a Flip Monster from Deck face-down and she can also Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from your GY if she was tributed and sent there. Her Flip Effect can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she is face-up on the field, she gives your Ritual Monsters targeting and destruction protection from your opponent's effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent's side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it. So before going into the F.A. monsters, all of them can increase their Level by 1 each time an F.A. Spell/Trap Card or effect is activated and their ATK is equal to their Level x300. 1 F.A. Dark Dragster which must first be Special Summoned from hand if you control a Level 7 or higher F.A. monster with no Dark Dragster on field. And it can also reduce its Level by 3 to pop a card on field. 3 F.A. Hang On Mach and 3 F.A. Whip Crosser. I can care less about what their unique monster effects are. We just need them to increase their Levels. 1 F.A. Auto Navigator. This is only in here as a possibility for a Synchro play. We aren't actually Synchroing for a Level 9 for our main plays, so 1 is enough. It does not increase its Level each time an F.A. Spell/Trap Card or effect is activated. If it's in hand or GY, you can target an F.A. whose Level is hgiher than its original Level, you can Special Summon this card and return that monster to its original Level and make Auto Nav's Level be equal to the amount reduced. And if it is Normal or Special Summon, you can search for an F.A. Field Spell. 

Spell/Traps: 3 U.A. Hyper Stadium which is also always treated as an F.A. card. On activation, it can add a U.A. or F.A. from Deck to hand or a U.A. Stadium from GY to hand. Also, you can reveal a Field Spell in hand and pay 1000 Life Points to have an Extra Normal Summon of a U.A. or an F.A. during your Main Phase this turn. Hyper Stadium basically gives an F.A. 2 additional Levels from its activation and its effect activation. 3 F.A. City Grand Prix which increases the Levels of all F.A. monsters on field by 2 during the Main and Battle Phase and gives your F.A. monsters targeting protection. If it is destroyed while face-up on field, you can add an F.A. card from Deck to hand. 2 F.A. Off-Road Grand Prix which increases the Levels of all F.A. monsters on field by 2 during the Main Phase. And it has the same searching effect on destruction as City Grand Prix. We are not playing F.A. Circuit Grand Prix because that card only increases Levels during the Battle Phase. 1 Terraforming. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites and 2 Prediction Ritual because we really need something to do if we don't draw our 3-card combo. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a Prediction Princess Ritual Monster from hand or GY face-up or face-down, and you can also banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from Deck face-down. And finally, 2 World Legacy Monstrosity which Special Summons a Level 9 from hand or targets a Level 9 you control and Special Summons 2 Level 9's from Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster, but with different names.

Extra Deck: 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 1 Baronne de Fleur. 1 F.A. Motorhome Transport. This card is pretty meh. It's basically a large body that is indestructible at Level 11 and it can reborn an F.A. every turn at Level 13. With City Grand Prix, it is also untargetable, but the card is still very meh. 1 F.A. Dawn Dragster which can reduce its Level by 2 once per turn to negate the activation of an opponent's Spell/Trap Card or effect. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which adds a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell from Deck to hand if sent to GY. 1 Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder. 1 Infinitrack Earth Slicer. 2 Mereologic Aggregator. 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller. 

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 1 Kurikara Divincarnate, 3 Dark Ruler No More, 2 Lightning Storm, 3 Evenly Matched, and 3 Infinite Impermanence.

Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Sean Pittman

Tournament: The Side Deck Gaming Café Remote WCQ Regional – December 10th 2023

Placement: Top 8
Destiny Board Dark Necrofear Deck

I was cooking in the Labratory when I came across Valient Smasher's Vaalmonica and while some might see a gimmicky archetype that's too slow to accomplish anything I saw its true potential, easy level 4 spam since the pendulums can summon level 4. So I looked for an archetype that had a bunch of powerful level 4s and the Yugi Archetype from the new set had some really powerful monsters. There are 3 and a half starters for the Vaalmonica archetype, Angello and Dimmono search each other, and their field spell can search them. Versare can search for a Vaalmonica however it is not exact and your opponent can give you a mill instead. For the Yugi cards if you don't open Golden Sarcophagous then you want to either search it with Gadet or search the Gadget with Silence towards the Future. This deck has a good grind game and will usually play a couple of turns setting up negates and destruction. Make sure to be careful if you activate Ties of Friendship because then you cannot special summon from the extra deck for the rest of the turn. Otherwise, it is very hard to play this deck incorrectly.

deck_excerpt: Fatal Abacus FTK ft. The Shallow Grave + Vampire Grace
deck_description:
Greetings! In this deck, we will FTK with Fatal Abacus alongside series of combinations. It's very complex and requires you to play fast, so read the guide with care.

 

 

Gameplan

1) At one point, discard either "Vampire Grace" or "Fusion Parasite" with Ravenous. You can alternatively discard both but no need to. Also, activate "Abyss Dweller" to not be disturbed due to your opponent's GY.

2) Then, Link Summon Saryuja when you have 4 cards in Main Deck to shuffle back all three "Fatal Abacus" and Special Summon one of them with Saryuja. I picked "Fusion Parasite" to bring forth "The Dark Magicians" as soon as I could. Otherwise, use "Monster Reborn" for your needs.

3) Place "ME-PSY-YA" on Pendulum Zone and Special Summon "Chaos Emperor Dragon" to setup "Primal Seed" loop. Just don't banish any one of these monsters explained above with Chaos Emperor and you are good.

4) Destroy and revive "The Dark Magicians" with Offerings + Reborn combination to draw and set all three "Fatal Abacus" but don't activate them just yet. Then, do the same for "Vampire Grace" and send four monsters from their Main Deck to GY.

5) Play "The Shallow Grave" to Special Summon monsters as face-down to not let your opponent disturb you. Since it requires both parties to Special Summon, activate "Back to Square One" to free up space from your side, if you must. Repeat this step until you have brought forth all of your opponent's monsters to their field.

6) Activate all three "Fatal Abacus" and play "Raigeki" to destroy your opponent's monsters and deal (500 x 4) x 3 = 6000 damage in total.

7) Repeat these steps explained in #5 and #6 to win the game!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "The Dark Magicians" can be collected by purchasing "Vortex of Magic" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Monster Reborn" + "Raigeki" are given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 60 UR!

- "Ravenous" + "Pot of Acquisitiveness" + "Fusion Parasite" + "Primal Seed" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 90 SR and 60 UR!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Abyss Dweller" can be found within "The Noble Knights of Crimson Flowers" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 540 SR and 240 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. Let me know if you have any questions and have fun in Master Duel!

deck_name: SD Battle City Box / Chimera the Flying
deck_description: SD Battle City Box / Chimera the Flying

This deck is built around the potential abuse of Nadir Servant. Going first, you use Nadir to send Garura from the ED, searching Maximus and drawing a card. Next, you banish Garura to special summon Maximus and use his effect to send Shuraig and Titaniklad. Shuraig now triggers, and since Garura is banished you can search Ponix, turning on your Fire King plays and setting up for either a Garunix wipe or a Kirin pop. In the end phase Titaniklad triggers, searching Fleur for additional disruption.

 

The side deck comes entirely from the structure deck and is focused almost entirely on board breaking. I decided to main 2 Dogoran with a third in the side to act as an out for ExNoir and other annoying monsters the 9 hand traps can't stop. Going first, you'll want to remove the kaijus and either Called By or one of the continuous spells for the playset of Judgment. Going second depends on the matchup, but Dark Hole, Alpha, and Herald should give you plenty of options. I used the flex spot for a second Sky Burn for longer games, but it could easily be Sacred Phoenix or High Avatar Garunix.

 

For upgrades, you should replace the maindeck Kaijus with Triple Tac or Nibiru. The side deck doesn't have anything to answer backrow, so it would be worth the space to swap Alpha and the flex card for either a playset of Cosmic Cyclone or a Feather Duster and 2 Lighting Storm. From there it's up to you: you can add a Thrustboard, or some Bystials to help against Labrynth and Unchained. From there you should look into trading Dogmatika for Diabellstarr and updating your extra deck with cards like Zeus, Little Knight, and TY-PHON.

deck_excerpt: NO WAY, A DECK THAT CAN OTK UNDER PROSPERITY??!??!

deck_description:
Instead of relying on Diabellstarr to access Snake-Eye lines, this list focuses on the insane value Ash + Populus can generate.

 

The main combo starts with the normal summon of Ash, then using Ash to search Pop, who then triggers to ss herself. Her effect sets the Sinful Spoil, which you use to trade Pop for Ponix. You can then chainblock the Ponix search with Pop's graveyard effect. From here you can run through the standard Amblowhale combo.

 

Of course, this is a budget deck. If you're looking for a few upgrades make sure to add Zeus and/or TY-PHON, as well as Little Knight to the ED. Additionally, you should upgrade the side deck.

deck_name: Fire King Dogmatika (Post YCS Bologna December 2023)
deck_description:
Hello there !

If you don't want to invest so much money in a Diabellstar engine, this build is made for you. I tried to make a Fire King list with a Dogmatika package to up the consistency with some spices. The reason of this build (and Diabellstar too) is to maximize your accesses to the best card of your deck : Ponix.

Pros/Cons

Pros : Increase your access to Ponix, add disruptions / draw power, less dependant to the Extra Deck => more space, synergy with Super Polymerization, possible to play Pot of Prosperity without too many conflicts (it can if you play it before Nadir Servant)

Cons : Hard lose to Droll, Lock in the Extra Deck => if Nadir Servant is your only access to your Fire King engine, you will not be able to use your Extra Deck toolbox

Budgets Options

  • Pot of Prosperity => 2 Fire Formation Tenki  + One for One : I consider Pot of Prosperity as not that expensive (thanks to the Rarity collection). However, you could consider those other options to replace it if you don't have/want to run Prosperity
  • S:P Little Knight => Knightmare Unicorn
  • Ty-phon => you could replace it by a Heatsoul for exemple
  • For the Maximus targets, Wind Pegasus @Ignister can be an option as well as Bucephalus

Deck Strategy

This variant is more focus on a heavy ressource management gameplay ; the Dogmatika package reduces your ability to make huge combos with the Extra deck and your plays will be more focused on your Fire King engine, setting your disruptions, getting your freespots to control your opponent during his turn. The deck has a great OTK potential (with the Garunix Xyz + Circle for exemple) and has a great ability to generate and recycle ressources. Furthermore, Nadir Servant locks you to summon Extra Deck monsters in some cases but the rest of the time, the deck has also many Extra Deck tools to control the pace of the game, recover ressources, managing some complex threats, ...

This is a sample list with my preferences : feel free to you to switch some free spots, to add some package as your convinience.

Do not hesitate to share your advices and your feedbacks about this list ! Enjoy :)

deck_excerpt: Not only is Branded a fusion strategy, they are now a synchro deck in Masterduel!
deck_description:
The arrival of the Masterduel pack "Beginning of the Next Journey" gives Albaz and friends the ability to extend EVEN FURTHER BEYOND the regular Branded strategy! Not only is Branded a fusion strategy, they are now a synchro deck! 
 
All the end phase effects of the strategy coupled with the deck's new starlet - Guiding Quem, turn the end phase into what duelists jokingly call "Main Phase 3" due to the ridiculous combos that are now possible. Sure, Ash Blossom on Branded Fusion still hurts, but this deck isn't centralized on this starter anymore - Branded can do so much more now! Synchro plays are available with the new floodgate trap card Branded Etude, allowing the pilot to synchro summon a level 10 synchro monster during your opponent's turn like Baronne De Fleur. Nadir Servant is granted enhanced usefulness as well, with its new target to send to the GY "Despian Luluwalilith." In the GY, she is able to summon either Cartesia (fusion on opponent's turn) or Quem (combo piece) in the end phase! 
 
It is safe to say that with the new support, Branded does not wholly rely on Branded Fusion anymore (even though it's still essential) and it can do a wide variety of other plays. Extension and different combo routes Quem and Luluwalilith offer allow the strategy to extend even after Nibiru, Maxx "C" Droll and Ash Blossom - four common and debilitating handtraps that would usually end your turn. Although your singular Branded Fusion is still extremely important to resolve, Branded can do so much more with Nadir Servant and Synchro plays!
 
ARCHETYPES AND DECKBUILDING
 
This variant of Branded is played "pure" only using cards that are native and related to the archetype. 
 
Other supplementary fusion support engines like Superpoly, Frightfur or King of the Swamp are not used, since room is needed for the Maxx "C" package. Unfortunately, the Maxx "C" package is mandatory if a deck wants to get far in Masterduel Ladder. With your rival's weakened board, you can usually break through with the Branded cards themselves. 
 
A sizeable portion of the deck are Bystials and their related cards, since they simultaneously act as starters, combo pieces and handtraps for the deck. Although Bystials aren't as effective since many common metagame threats aren't light or dark attribute (Kashtira and Vanquish Soul), they are still essential to the Branded strategy. Also, level 6s Bystials are perfect for synchro summoning Baronne!
 
Dramaturge of Despia and Ad Libitum of Despia are replaced by two Quem, since the decks combos have changed dramatically since her introduction. Since Quem always counts as a "Despia" card, she will can also be summoned with Branded Opening. Quem also counts as a "Dogmatika" card, so she can be summoned if Titaniklad is sent to the GY. 
 
Depite it's Extra Deck lock, Nadir Servant now serves as an extender and starter for Branded, eventually searching/summoning both Cartesia and Quem by the End Phase through the dump of Luluwalilith. Even if Branded Fusion gets negated, Nadir Servant allows the Branded player to continue extending and to fusion summon during the opponent's turn. 
 
6 cards make Branded fusion directly searchable (2 Aluber, 2 Branded Opening, 1 Springans Kitt and 1 Branded Fusion). In hands where Cartesia, Albion the Shrouded Dragon and Bystial Saronir are present, the duelist can also search any Branded card, including Branded Fusion. This combo makes Branded Fusion readily accessible in most opening hands (50 cards aren't bricky, and they're optimal I swear! COPIUM ). 
 
COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN
 
As usual, the Branded strategy revolves around resolving Branded Fusion and summoning giant beatsticks with interruptions on field while generating immense resource advantage to outgrind your opponent. After allowed to resolve all your effects, you probably will have 5-7 cards in hand at the conclusion of End Phase! 
 
Quem and Luluwalilith's entry into the Branded strategy grants this deck increased flexibility and resilience. The deck can play through handtraps that would normally end a turn like Ash Blossom and Nibiru. Nadir Servant is almost as impactful as Branded Fusion, since it represents both Cartesia and Quem on board. 
 
Depending on the quality of the hand, what cards you start with and the interruptions from your opponent, the Branded player's board will vary. Here are the combos for post "Beginning of the Next Journey" Branded Synchro: 
 
ULTIMATE BRANDED COMBO aka the famous "Main Phase 3" --------- Aluber + Bystial Magnamhut + Any Card: 
= Mirrorjade (Banish), Quem (Reborn Mirrorjade for another Banish), Cartesia (Fusion summon Granguignol + Mirrorjade into Dragostapelia's monster negate), Granguignol (Summon Luluwalilith for negate), Branded Etude (Bystial + Cartesia = Baronne) (Banish Floodgate), Mercourier (Monster Negate). 
  1. Normal summon Aluber. Search Branded Fusion. 
  2. Activate Branded Fusion to summon Rindbrumm, sending Albaz + Mercourier. 
  3. Activate Magnamhut targeting Mercourier in the GY, banishing it. 
  4. CL1 Mercourier (searching Cartesia) and CL2 Magnumhut to search dragon in End Phase. 
  5. Activate Cartesia to summon to field since Albaz is in GY. Activate Cartesia to fusion summon Granguignol using herself + Aluber. 
  6. Granguignol effect sends from Extra Deck Sprind to the GY. 
  7. Proceed to End Phase (Now the REAL combo begins!). Retrieve Cartesia from GY. Magnamhut searches for Saronir. 
  8. Sprind summons from deck Springans Kitt. Kitt searches for Branded in High Spirits from deck and places any card in hand to bottom of deck. 
  9. Activate Branded in High Spirits revealing and discarding Saronir in hand and sending Titaniklad from Extra Deck to GY.  High Spirits then adds Mercourier to hand. In a new chain, the discarded Saronir sends Branded Retribution to GY.
  10. Titaniklad summons from deck Quem. Quem sends to GY Branded in Red. 
  11. Activate Branded Retribution in GY to retrieve Branded in Red from GY to hand. 
  12. Activate Branded in Red targeting Albaz in GY. Fusion summon Lubellion using Albaz + Kitt. 
  13. CL1 Lubellion to fusion summon Mirrorjade shuffling itself + Albaz back into the decks by discarding Cartesia, CL2 Quem to summon Cartesia from GY.
  14. Activate Mirrorjade's effect to send to GY Albion. In a new chain, activate Rindbrumm's effect to negate Mirrorjade's effect (so you can still use its banish effect next turn) then you can bounce Magnamhut back to hand so you can re-use it next turn.
  15.  Albion sets Branded Etude from deck. 
This is the ultimate combo that Branded is capable of post-CYAC! 
 
Potential two non-targeting banishes with Mirrorjade because Quem can reborn Mirrorjade from the GY. Cartesia can fusion summon Granguignol + Mirrorjade for Dragostapelia for a monster negate. Granguignol can summon Luluwalilith from Extra Deck, which is another negate. Magnumhut can banish from either player's GY their light/dark monster. Baronne De Fleur can be synchro summoned through Branded Etude using Cartesia/Quem + Magnamhut for an omni-negate. Finally, Mercourier can negate a monster effect. That's a whopping potential SEVEN interruptions for your opponent! 
 
If your opponent hasn't surrendered to your onslaught, you have so much follow-up for next turn's counter-offensive! Mirrorjade has dumped Albion, searching for you any Branded card in the end phase. Cartesia returns to your hand. Branded in High Spirits returns to hand as well. Magnamhut searches any Dragon from deck. Your hand will likely be 5-7 cards after your End Phase!
 
BRANDED FUSION GOT ASHED/NEGATED! --------- Quem/Cartesia + Nadir Servant + Any Card (Discard) = Quem + Cartesia + Mirrorjade + Branded Fusion and another Branded card as follow-up. 
  1. Branded Fusion got ASHED. Have no fear! Summon Quem/Cartesia. If you summoned Quem, send to GY any Branded card. Branded Retribution is ideal here, so you can retrieve your Branded Fusion to use when its your turn again. 
  2. Activate Nadir Servant, sending Luluwalilith to GY and search for Albaz. 
  3. Proceed to End Phase. Summon Cartesia/Quem (whichever one you're missing) from deck with the effect of Luluwalilith. 
  4.  During your opponent's Main Phase, activate Cartesia's effect to fuse Cartesia + Albaz in hand for Albion. 
  5. CL1 Albion's effect to fuse into Mirrorjade, using Albaz and Luluwalilith in Grave. CL2 Quem's effect to summon Cartesia from graveyard. 
While getting your Branded Fusion negated isn't ideal, with Nadir Servant and the new support, it is still possible to make Mirrorjade during your opponent's turn! Not only that, you obtain follow up by recycling Branded Fusion in GY with Branded Retribution. As your Mirrorjade banishes a monster on field, it will also dump Albion to the GY grabbing you more follow-up (Any Branded Card) for next turn! With this combo, a negated Branded Fusion isn't the end of the duel for the Branded pilot. 
 
GENERAL TIPS
  • Due to the excess of tuners on board, sometimes it is better to follow up on the counterattack not with Branded Fusion (since it locks you into fusions), but with synchro summons. Lvl 6 Bystial + Cartesia/Quem make Baronne, while any level 8 dragon + Cartesia/Quem makes Luluwalilith! Both these ladies push for OTK very easily, with Baronne's pop and Lulu's fieldwide ATK boost. 
  • Don't underestimate Etude of the Branded coupled with a Bystial on board since it can ruin some unprepared strategies if they can't out either card. Banishing opponent's material used for Ritual, Fusion, Synchro and Link summons renders meta decks like Tearlament and Mathmech near unplayable! 
  • With Quem both and Mirrorjade on board, you can actually use Mirrorjade's banish effect twice in the same turn! After Mirrorjade leaves the field (most likely used as Synchro/Fusion material) Quem can re-summon Mirrorjade from the GY so it can banish once again! 
  • To make your board immune to Nibiru as you combo, try to obtain Mercourier early. If you already have Branded Fusion, search Branded Lost instead so when you fusion summon, you can get Mercourier. 
  • Be mindful you only have two Albaz in deck. Try to recycle (Lubellion/Branded Lost) and shuffle it back into deck as much as possible so you can keep using Branded Fusion. 
CONCLUDING REMARKS
 
Albaz finally did it. He triumphed over his enemies with the power of friendship and love (classic "shounen" anime moment lol)! For the time being, the nefarious Aluber and crew take a break, having their goals accomplished. With that, the support for Branded reaches its apex with Masterduel's "Beginning of the Next Journey" pack (until season 2 of "Branded" comes out)! 

The incredible conclusion of the Abyss Storyline brings some incredible cards to the Branded strategy. Quem enabling "main phase 3" and other combo routes propels the deck to even higher power levels than ever before so it can fight toe-to-toe with Masterduel meta heavyweights such as Kashtira, Purrely, Mathmech and Vanquish Soul. Just like how Albaz and friends overcame adversity, suffering and trials, you can overcome your opponent with the powerful new tools Branded received!

GLHF Duelists!

deck_description:
My take on Yami Yugi's Deck (the illusion created by Kaiba) in Dark Side of Dimensions.

Decided to differentiate this and regular Yugi's Deck (because, not only would it make sense in-canon imo, as it helps show off the huge amount of new cards that were released in the movie consistently).

I also added a few other cards that would make sense to appear in his Deck (except the anime-only cards, unfortunately).

Feel free to give your opinion on this Deck, as this will most likely not be its final version (this isn't even the first version I've made for their Decks, actually).

(Didn't use cards that were banned in 2016 for these Decks, but decided to use cards that would be released later.)

---

PS: Does anyone know how to alternate card artworks in here?? I can't seem to find where and how to do it

Here is a Naturia deck. I made this because I was thinking about making a deck that includes a lot of fruit. I noticed that most of the fruit cards happened to be the Naturia cards. So I made a deck of that archetype which was already cool, but I added other fruit themed cards like Fengli. Enjoy :)
Testing out some combinations

My take on Yugi Muto's Deck in Dark Side of Dimensions.

Decided to differentiate this deck from the Virtual Copy created by Kaiba of Atem (because, not only would it make sense in-canon imo, as it helps show off the huge amount of new cards that were released in the movie consistently).

I also added a few other cards that would make sense to appear in his Deck (except the anime-only cards, unfortunately).

Feel free to give your opinion on this Deck, as this will most likely not be its final version (this isn't even the first version I've made for their Decks, actually).

(Didn't use cards that were banned in 2016 for these Decks, but decided to use cards that would be released later.)

---

And I personally think Mahad should not be placed normally in his Deck (it almost seems like Yugi drew it from thin air because of the Pharaoh), so I kept it in the Side Deck (right next to other cards that could have been in it).

PS: Does anyone know how to alternate card artworks in here?? I can't seem to find where and how to do it

My take on Seto Kaiba's Deck from DSOD.

I decided to focus more on Blue-Eyes here but didn't use any Synchro and Xyz monsters for consistency with the timeline.

I also added a few other cards that would make sense to appear in his Deck (except the anime-only cards, unfortunately).

Feel free to give your opinion on this Deck, as this will most likely not be its final version (this isn't even the first version I've made for their Decks, actually).

(Didn't use cards that were banned in 2016 for these Decks, but decided to use cards that would be released later.)

 

---

There's no way that Kaiba had Obelisk in his Deck before - he literally screwed the rules just to summon it lol.
